ch.se.inf.ethz.jcd.batman.vdisk.impl

Class VirtualFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.se.inf.ethz.jcd.batman.vdisk.impl.VirtualDiskEntry
      • ch.se.inf.ethz.jcd.batman.vdisk.impl.VirtualFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IVirtualDiskEntry, IVirtualFile, java.lang.Iterable<IVirtualDiskEntry>

    public final class VirtualFile
extends VirtualDiskEntry
implements IVirtualFile
    Implementation of IVirtualFile. The file contains two separate IVirtualDiskSpace on stores the meta data of the file and one stores the data of the file. The IVirtualDiskSpace which handles the meta data is structured as follows: 0x00 1 Entry Type 0x01 8 Time stamp 0x09 8 Offset position of the next directory/file which is stored in the same directory as this directory 0x11 8 Offset position of the IVirtualDiskSpace of the data 0x19 n File name

        public void seek(long position)

        Sets the offset position, measured in bytes from the beginning of the file. The offset may be set beyond the end of the file. Setting the offset beyond the end of the file does not change the file length. The file length will change only by writing after the offset has been set beyond the end of the file.
